Sam Wilson just can't catch a break. Ever since he took on the mantle of Captain America (which was bestowed upon him by the original Steve Rogers) he has become a political lightning rod, inadvertently inciting divisiveness wherever the hero goes. In this retrospective, we take a deep look at Nick Spencer's take on the Sentinel of Liberty and why Sam's turn with the shield was met with so much controversy. Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [ComicBookClique.com](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media. Send us feedback at ComicBookClique@Gmail.com! You Are Worthy! Please [SUPPORT US ON PATREON](http://Patreon.com/CBCClubhouse)!

